HEADWORD: Stillson wrench
<hw>Still"son wrench</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A pipe wrench having an
adjustable <universbold>L</universbold>-shaped jaw piece sliding in a
sleeve that is pivoted to, and loosely embraces, the handle. Pressure on
the handle increases the grip.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stillstand</ent>⟦br⟧
